<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/27 (Thu.) Is cohabitation wrong? / Nomophobia (Host: Danny)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=241&amp;p=255#p255"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">Session 1: Is cohabitation wrong?</span><br /><br />Here are debates over the issue of cohabitation, please check the link below, and pick some opinions for your references.<br /><a href="https://www.debate.org/opinions/is-cohabitation-wrong" class="postlink">https://www.debate.org/opinions/is-cohabitation-wrong</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1.Is cohabitation wrong? If not, please tell your table members why?<br />2.What are the pros and cons of cohabitation?<br />3.Do men or women get the most benefits of cohabitation?<br />4.Many young people now think that marriage costs a lot of money and energy, while cohabitation costs them nothing. Still, some consider cohabitation as a trial when some think it as cheating? Any thoughts about that? <br />5.As Socrates Quotes. “By all means, marry. If you get a good wife, you'll become happy; if you get a bad one, you'll become a philosopher”. What’s your interpretation about it?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 2: Nomophobia</span><br /><br />Please find the video below,<br /><a href="http://www.fox5ny.com/279053126-video" class="postlink">http://www.fox5ny.com/279053126-video</a><br /><br />Here are some tips for you to see if you have nomophobia?<br />• You never turn your phone off<br />• You obsessively check for texts, missed calls and emails<br />• You always take your phone to the bathroom with you<br />• You never let the battery run out<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1.Do you have nomophobia? Any other symptoms you know expecting these above? Do you think it as nothing or could it be something that’s currently affecting your life?<br />2.Have you ever left your phone behind when you were going to somewhere? Please share you story of how you felt and how you dealt with it? <br />3.What causes people so obsessive to their smart phone? Try to think of 3 reasons for it and explain why?<br />4.Let’s put ourselves in a scenario: If you’re a boss leading a company, but you’ve been wondering that your employees are busy for their work or texting their friends? Be honest and put yourself in the boss’s shoes, would you just directly ban them from using social media at office, or Sneaked behind them and see what’s going on? Or just let them use it freely for the concern of privacy?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Agenda</span><br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />8:10 ~ 8:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:25 ~ 8:30pm Regrouping<br />(Session II)<br />8:30 ~9:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">The meeting place of Thursday:</span><br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=827">Jason Tang</a> — Thu Dec 20, 2018 10:46 pm</p><hr />
